<TITLE> All allowances to rise in new budget </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 20 (bdnews24.com) All the allowances under social security programme, including the ones for the elderly, freedom fighters and widows, and the number of beneficiaries will increase in the upcoming budget which is at the final stages, the finance minister has said. "We are committed to increase all the allowances under the social security scheme. It was our election pledge," A M A Muhith said on Wednesday after an inter-ministerial meeting on old age allowance at the Secretariat. But the final decision on how much the raise and how many the number will be is yet to be taken, he said. Budget for the 2009-10 fiscal year is at the final stages, said finance minister Abul Maal Abdul Muhith. "All works will be done within this month. Then it will be sent to the press," he said his office on Wednesday. The budget session will start on June 4 and it will be presented at the parliament on June 11. In the current 2008-09 fiscal year, around 20 lakh poor elderly people are being given Tk 250 as a monthly allowance and one lakh poor freedom fighters are receiving Tk 900 monthly allowance. "The amount for the elderly can be increased to Tk 300 and the number of beneficiaries can be increased to 22 lakhs," said a finance ministry official told bdnews24.com, preferring anonymity as he was not supposed to speak to the media. "The allowance for the freedom fighters will be increased to Tk 1,500 keeping the number of beneficiaries unchanged," he said. Besides, nine lakh widows, destitute women and women abandoned by their husbands are receiving Tk 250 monthly allowance. Sixty-thousand women are receiving Tk 300 a month under poor maternity allowance scheme under the current budget. bd
